text: Elias Kuukka (born 1994) is a Finnish orienteering competitor, born in Tampere. He competed at the 2019 World Orienteering Championships in Østfold, where placed 14th in the long distance, and won a silver medal with the Finnish relay team, along with Aleksi Niemi and Miika Kirmula. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:People from Tampere Category:Finnish orienteers Category:Male orienteers Category:Foot orienteers Category:Competitors at the 2017 World Games Category:World Orienteering Championships medalists
